    \foreach \y in {1,...,8} {
      \ifodd\y \even\x
        \put\chessboardcell[\x*1.5cm,y*1.5cm]{\Pawn}
      \else
        \put\chessboardcell[\x*1.5cm,y*1.5cm]{\empty}
      \fi
    }
  }
\end{chessboard}
```

4. Finally, add the following code to compile the document:

```latex
\end{document}
```

When you compile your LaTeX document, it will generate a chessboard with FEN notation based on the FEN1 notation.

Note: Since you need to include chess pieces symbols, you might need to use additional packages (e.g., "tikz-chess") to support Unicode characters. However, the above examples should work with the "chessboard" package by Tigris.

