```java
public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
    if (n <= 0) {
        return false;
    }

    while (n!= 1 && n % 3 == 0) {
        n = n / 3;
    }

    return n == 1;
}
```

This function checks if the given integer `n` is a power of three. If `n` is less than or equal to 0, the function returns `false`. Otherwise, the function checks if `n` is divisible by 3 and keeps dividing it by 3 until it becomes 1 or not divisible by 3 anymore. If the final value of `n` is 1, the function returns `true`, meaning `n` is a power of three; otherwise, it returns `false`.

This solution has a time complexity of O(log(n)) due to the while loop iterating at most log(n) times.

